---
<DocsLayout title="Automation">
  <h1>Automation</h1>

  <h2>Cron jobs</h2>
  <p>
    Cron jobs are best for precise schedules. If you want a morning brief every day at 7:30 AM,
    a cron job is the right tool.
  </p>

  <h2>Heartbeats</h2>
  <p>
    Heartbeats are better for lightweight periodic checks that can drift a bit. They are useful when
    you want an agent to periodically check a short task list and only speak up when something needs attention.
  </p>

  <h2>Example use cases</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Daily calendar + weather briefings</li>
    <li>Inbox summaries</li>
    <li>Recurring project status checks</li>
    <li>Quiet background memory maintenance</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
